# Next.js Frontend — UniSchedule AI

## Stack

- Next.js (App Router preferred), TypeScript, fetch/axios to Laravel API

## API client

- Base URL from `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`
- Attach Sanctum token on every request:

```typescript
headers: {
  Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`,
  Accept: 'application/json',
}
```

- Handle 401 → redirect to login; 422 → show validation errors

## Pages (minimum)

- Login / register (student vs lecturer)
- Dashboard — list meetings
- Book meeting — form + optional natural language input
- Clash feedback UI — show alternatives when API returns conflicts

## Do not

- Put scheduling business rules only in the frontend — clash/constraint logic lives in **Laravel**
- Store Sanctum token in localStorage if avoiding XSS — prefer httpOnly cookie pattern when using Sanctum SPA setup
- Call LLM APIs directly from browser for booking (keys exposed) — route through Laravel

## UI

- Accessible forms, clear clash/error messages
- Loading and error states on all API calls
